from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# We'll drop the [Registered, Casual, Holiday] column (Because Holiday has already been represented by workingday)

X = train.reset_index().drop(['cnt','registered','casual','holiday'],axis=1).values #splitting the features and target variable
X_colnames = train.drop(['cnt','registered','casual','holiday'],axis=1).columns #Extracting the column names for later usage
y = train.reset_index().cnt.values

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)



    















=============================================== Feature Selection =============================================













In [245]:



    


#We'll use Recursive Feature Selection combined with Random Forest Regressor to determine the least significant variable
from sklearn.feature_selection import RFE
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
rf_for_rfe = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100,random_state=42) #We'll use 100 trees
selector = RFE(rf_for_rfe,6,step=1) #Selecting 6 best variable from a total of 11 variable, 
#(the last 5 variable will be ranked from best candidate to worst)
selector.fit(X_train[:,1:],y_train)
rfe_ranking = pd.Series(selector.ranking_, index=X_colnames)
rfe_ranking.plot(kind='barh')
plt.title('feature selection for best 6 features (lower is better)')
plt.show()



    















    




























Findings: windspeed are ranked lowest, this can be explained by the fact that people doesn't care that much about windspeed when riding a bike unless there is some unusually high windspeed















Conclusion : let's drop windspeed variable

In [283]:



    


model = Sequential()
monitor_val_acc = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5) #Earlystopping based on val_loss with patience of 5 step
#First Hidden Layer with 200 nodes and 57 input nodes, relu activation
model.add(Dense(200,activation='relu',input_shape=(57,),kernel_initializer='normal'))

#Second Hidden Layer with 100 nodes, relu activation
model.add(Dense(100,activation='relu',kernel_initializer='normal'))

#Third Hidden Layer with 50 nodes, relu activation
model.add(Dense(50,activation='relu',kernel_initializer='normal'))

#Fourth Hidden Layer with 20 nodes, relu activation
model.add(Dense(20,activation='relu',kernel_initializer='normal'))

#Output layer, relu activation
model.add(Dense(1,activation='relu',kernel_initializer='normal'))

#Adam optimizer with mean squared logarithmic error losses
model.compile(optimizer='adam',loss='msle')
